  \put\transclude/title{featured talks}
  \query{
    \query/and{
      \query/author{jonmsterling}
      \query/taxon{reference}
      \query/tag{featured}
    }
  }
}]]></fr:pre><fr:p>Under the hood, a query node is an “anonymous transclusion” and can therefore be <fr:link
href="jms-0067.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-0067">configured using the same options as other transclusions</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:contributions></fr:contributions><fr:context><fr:tree
